721132f-a.title: Manhattan: Lispenard Street - Broadway (West)
721132f-a.text:
Nos. 1 to 9 Lispenard Street, at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of West Broadway (left, Sixth Ave. Elevated line thereon), as viewed northward from Sixth Ave. Extension (foreground). At the extreme right margin is a portion of the New York Telephone Building.
May 1, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.

721133f-a.title: Manhattan: Lispenard Street - Broadway (West)
721133f-a.text:
Lisbenard Street, east from a point between West Broadway and Church Street and across the latter to Broadway. The clearing at the left is the southerly half of that block between Lispenard and Canal Street and extends to Church Street. Upon the easterly side of the latter is a gas station; the buildings appearing beyond same facing on Canal and Lispenard Streets. To the left is Canal Street, with the Logan Building (sign atop) at the N.E. corner of same and Greene Street.
May 7, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
